,Recommended,240760,24925936,"Posted: 14 August, 2016",all,Ozymandias,"Just as a warning, this game starts off extremely frustrating. Ammo management can screw you over in the opening hours and you can easily make some mistakes in skill allotment that further set you back early on if you don't know what you're doing. I probably have 8-10 skill points I've completely wasted just because I wasn't sure exactly sure what to expect, which is sort of a bummer, but it is nice to have some consequences to your decisions.Some boss encounters are also really annoying, and can waste big chunks of unsaved progress. No spoilers or anything, but more than once I've just randomly had someone who I thought was a friend turn on me in the middle of a conversation and lay waste to my unprepared guys. Some auto-saves before these points would really be appreciated.That being said, once you get past the first 3-5 hours ammo is much easier to acquire (buy/loot, safecracking skill is very useful here) and you get much better and more diversified weapons, and the combat really opens up.Additionally, the world is interesting to explore. Great setting, great characters, and a very diverse set of areas/locations to traverse. It isn't afraid to be dark/macabre, which is a nice change of pace from more recent post nuclear war RPGs...The game does feel a little low budget, which is understandable given how it was made, but it's been fine as far as stability. I can't recall any crashes.Overall, a very good game. Frustrating initially, but when you get your hooks in it's a ton of fun. I was not expecting at all to sink this much time into it."
