d guy, a not so much good guy, or an ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ (who'd want to do that?). You can talk to someone important and sweet talk him him into giving you a key to open a certain door, you can use a party member to use a lock pick skill on that said door, or you can also just shoot a missile at the same door to blast it open, too. What I'm trying to convey is that Wasteland 2 is giving you plenty of options to complete your objective, and you'll have a lot them to complete. Some of those objectives, depending on how/when you complete them, can reward you later on. So, if you're going to play like an ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥, be prepared to be treated like an ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥. No complaining."
