76561198031459474,Not Recommended,240760,12342621,"Posted: 3 October, 2014",all,haplok,"I would love to recommend this game.Unfortunately I cannot. It was advertised as a spiritual successor to Fallout 1 & 2 and sadly it is nowhere near the quality of these games.Given the credentials of the creators of this game, the fundamental issues it has have been a major dissapointment to me.I could look over the simple, passable if shallow combat system in what was supposed to be a crpg, but mostly is a tactical squad shooter.But hopelessly shallow and illogical crpg mechanics I cannot forgive.The attributes are very weak and have very little impact on gameplay, like maximum 10 Coordination gives +10 to hit - about as much as 1-2 ranks in the respective weapon skill. And less then what 1 weapon mod can give you...Speaking about skills, this system is awfully shallow, with no connection between attributes and skills. Yes, your 1 Strenght wimp will be just as good at bashing doors open, as a 10 Strenght champion strongman. Or your 1 Charisma cavemen will talk just as smoothly as your 10 Charisma face. There is a large number of skills, many of which are redundant (medic and surgeon, lockpicking and safe cracking, perception and outdoorsman, to a lesser degree the separate combat skills for each weapon type).Out of the attributes in the end only the derived stats Action Points and Combat Initiative really count.There are no perks/traits/talents.There is actually little incentive to keep levelling after the first 20 levels or so. As the skills check difficulty will invariably rise as the game goes on and only the highest skill ranks are worth anything,  you need to split the skill load between charcters. So on each level you get some more hp and some skill points, which you assign to the same skills you have chosen for each character at the beginning of the game. The levelling process could just as well be automated.Oh and you get a stat point... every 10 levels.There are no range accuracy modifiers, no aiming at and disabling different body parts.Terrible, random loot. What's with the hordes of containers and safes! spread seeingly randomly all over the place? Was it raining safes in Arizona or something? That's beyond silly. Oh and when you finally diffuse that trap and beat that impossible lock guarding that chest/safe, you will certainly feel very rewarded when you find 5 bullets and a glass eye inside. Don't expect valuable stashes of old technology hidden by some bosses/factions/military organizations/research centers, not in this game, no. Only a handfull of bullets for you. Better buy your guns at the local vendor... oh and that power armor too.Actually maybe don't. Armor... suffice to say it's horrible. In the end game it's much safer not to wear any...I would love to change my opinion if the devs can ""fix"" this game. Unfortunately there is so much wrong with it, that it would be a monumental task. Still, one can hope. It is pretty much my favourite genre and the game has a lot of potential.But that makes its fundamental flaws that much more painfull to me. It was so near, but so many design choices make absolutely no sense...."
