76561198014845737,Not Recommended,240760,12369316,"Posted: 4 October, 2014",all,Moter,"While I'm a big fan of turn-based strategy games ala Jagged Alliance, Silent Storm, Fallout, etc, I can't recommend this game in its current state.AI is such that enemies (unless equipped with a sniper rifle) will run straight up to your squad in order to inflict a to-hit penalty on your assault/sniper rifle squaddies, foregoing all cover on the way. This leads to repeated battles in which you move said squaddies 2 steps away, and kill said enemies effortlessly.Skill points are useless after around level 30 (3/4 through the game), as your specialized squad will have their assigned skills capped, and any more spending only results in overlap.There are still script/dialogue bugs to be fixed, as well as smaller issues such as items with grossly exaggerated weights.There are also some poorly-thought out mechanics:- ""Lost Control"" - NPCs that join you all have an inherent chance to go rogue, removing your ability to control them and imposing beeline-AI on their actions as described above.- Leadership skill - gives nearby squaddies a small chance-to-hit bonus within a small area, and reduces the chance for hirees to go rogue within that small area. Move those hirees outside the magic circle, and you risk losing control of them. Exacerbated by melee/ranged.- Animal Whisperer skill - you can tame animal companions... who don't have enough hp to survive one attack (and they will get attacked), and not only can you not control them, but some will attack, imposing beeline-AI as described above. The result? Expect any tamed companions to die in the next fight.Shelved until major update."
