,Recommended,240760,12150824,"Posted: 19 September, 2014",all,Allexio,"Now this game isnt bad, however, I recommend this game FOR HARDCORE TACTICAL RPGs FANS ONLY. If you are new to the genre, or if you don't really know, do NOT buy this now and wait for a reduction on the full price.Frankly this is a game I really would recommend you pirate before buying, especially if you're a casual gamer, you may not like this peculiar experience.Now lets be honest, I was not impressed when I first started playing this game. I was new to it, lots of stuff is unexplained (like the fact that you can blow up gates and such) and the game was a bit complex. After 40 hours of gameplay, I can say that this game is worth every penny of it's price. What this game lacks in graphics and in audio it catches up clearly with great combat mechanics and a very long story. Is the story good? No. At least, not the first part of it. However, all the plots that will unravel as you progress in the main story or the side plots are all quite exceptionnal. They all have different outcomes, which can completely reshape areas you were in previously. This game is fantastic in it's own distinct way. The universe is immersive (once again except for the poor character graphics and the bad audio) and sucks you into the game.With a bit more and really only a bit more effort in one or two updates, this game would get 9/10.All I'm asking for is a complete review of the OST of the game, the creating of a lot more character portraits, the remodelling of characters in general and the finishing of the spoken dialogue. With this relatively small amount of work, this game could really be outstanding.What follows is a break-up of the different things I experienced in game, in a bullet-point, non review-esque style.+ COMBAT: a solid combat system:10 different weapon types, including 3 melee weapon types (blunt, blade and brawl) and 7 close (shotguns, pistols, SMG) to medium (assault rifles, heavy weapons) to long (sniper rifles) range. With an extra emphasis on armor and some weapon types being very effective against heavy armor (energy weapons, a category in which there are weapons of all ranges) and some less.A cover system which sometimes bugs a bit.A crouch to aim better system.A headshot system that trades accuracy for extra damage.A ""when you shoot someone lower (in terms of altitude) than you, you get a bonus in accuracy"" systemSome hit ratios may seem a little low, the more you spend skill points in a weapon type, the more precise you become in your shots with it.+ EXPLORATION: Another well thought out systemYou will need to upgrade 11 different skills to survive in the wasteland, and by that I mean to efficiently explore every single area by destroying walls and lockpicking doors and gates and loot every single chest, safe...Don't forget to level up your perception skill to spot traps and mines and your demolition skill to disarm them.Your surgeon and field medic skills can help you a lot in the wastes, or rather, it can help the people around you a lot.The vision circle around your characters will be blocked by high objects, forcing you to move behind them making the game much more realistic.+ STORY:There are lots of different paths you can take throughout the main story and the side stories, which all affect each other in a way.To unlock different paths, don't forget to upgrade your 3 convincing skills, Hard-A-s-s, Kiss-A-s-s (which I think should've been called seduction but yeah whatever), and Smart-A-s-sAnd believe me, youll need them or you'll really be locked on one path instead of having the liberty to choose.* message to the creators of this game, an A-s-s is a donkey. The bottom is A-r-s-e not A-s-s!!! *+ I just sold pigeon droppings (and cow poo) for 1 dollar.- I just found out that instead of selling the pigeon droppings, I could've exchanged them against a rocket launcher. I feel cheated.+ Lots of readable stuff... if you want to take your time and read everything that happens... and a lot of things happen. When you see 15 lines of text appearing instantly when you walk in a completely normal place you can wonder what the point was, the fact that it is only written and not dialogued makes the reading a bit of a chore. Imagine having to stop every two seconds to read the paragraph of text that just appeared. Yeah. I support traditional text RPGs but I'm not so much a fan of what happens in between. Still, some pretty funny jokes, so yeah, it really depends on if you want to take your time and read everything. I would have preferred a complete spoken dialogue to paragraphs upon paragraphs upon paragraphs of text.+ The graphics are underrated. They frankly aren't that bad. In fact the environment looks pretty good.- When characters disobey orders, they act as if they have no brain and just run to the ennemy without even shooting their weapon.+ The narration that is in place is excellent...- ...Shame that it isn't complete ( AT ALL ), wouldve made for a better game experience.- Characters look ugly.- The same character portraits are used too often and do not correspond to what the character looks like.- The OST is poor. VERY poor. In fact in most places it seems non existent.- Not enough sniper ammo in crates, too much of the rest.- Sniper rifle seems op. Like in any other game.- Steam overlay is not accessible in-game.- No Steam achievements on a game that would be great with Steam achievements.- This game will force you to quicksave every half a second. Which can get annoyingbut is also good training for future life when you will have save your work every half a second by fear of losing it."
