76561198043602389,Recommended,240760,16431821,"Posted: 15 June, 2015",all,Tacticus Winter,"Wow......people say this isn't like Fallout. Of course it's not, but it certainly, without a doubt feels just like it. I felt the nostalgia all over me playing this.If you take Fallout and put it in a bed with Divinity: Original Sin or Pillars of Eternity, well, this is the result.Now to the break down.The Good:Combat(8.7/10)- Combat is smooth, feels so much like XCOM, a favorite of mine, and is strategically rewarding. It has a good amount of gore and the animations are done fantastically. There are a lot of weapons to use and each weapon is made accordingly making strategic planning and placement crucial.Gameplay(9.6/10)- I couldn't exit the game. I didn't want to. I wanted to keep playing. It has that perfect feel of ""Whats around this corner, whats in this box, whats in that cave"" you dont want to leave your screen. The voice acting, holy hell the voice acting, it's a work of beauty. And the graphics, the graphics fit perfectly, backgrounds and non-enterable areas are drawn out and made so beautifully.Story(8.5/10)- The story so far, is quite interesting as there is interesting plot changes, eerie coms messages and decisions in each and every corner of the game to question, explore, and discover. The gears in your mind turn and you keep wanting to find out more and more.Character(8.9/10)- I was immediately attached to my characters after I spent about 10 minutes creating my 4 custom squad-mates. I had Bill my strong charismatic Desert Ranger look. Kit, my hard♥♥♥♥♥big-mouthed spy-sniper chick. Liam, my Australian drugged mechanic, and Rico, the young suck-up, Combat medic from the Marines. The level of detail is amazing, the designs and amount of combinations are extreme.The Decent:AI(6.8/10)- The AI is OK. It's not that hard, but it's not that easy either. It has strategies, and tries it's best to use cover and enemy types use their weapons accordingly.Pathfinding(7.3/10)- Pathfinding, I have had a few issues with. In combat and walking around. Some party members stray off at times, and in combat some of them take odd directions when I told them not to take that direction. It's a rare annoyance but is very very nagging when it comes around.The downright terrible♥♥♥♥♥♥Saving(1.6/10)- There is no autosave. Simple. Well, there is one, but it's non-existant. My last autosave from my most recent manual save is 45 minutes ago. 45 MINUTES. That is♥♥♥♥♥♥ Terrible. And in a game like this there needs to be a working autosave.Combat UI(4.6/10)- The Combat UI is near useless. It skips out on basic features that you have to use your Inventory to view like how much ammo one person has on them, and how much armor before that person begins taking real damage. Also, the only health-bar you see is when you hover over that person. It's annoying, when a person is low on health, I will RARELY know that until they die. That leaves you constantly wasting a minute or 2 checking health and seeing how many med-packs you have left.OVERALL VERDICT (8.7/10):Wasteland 2 is a welcoming game that if you're new, you will quickly get the hang of it, and at the same time can be a brutal experience. It is fun, heart racing, and definitely a ""What's around the next corner"" game that I can easily, easily, sink 80 hours into.If these few nagging bugs can be fixed, it will make the experience a whole lot smoother. And with these issues fixed the verdict is an easy 9.3/10"
