,Recommended,240760,14021681,"Posted: 16 January, 2015",all,Fitz,"Reviewed after 28 hours of game time.Generally a good game however the combat becomes somewhat monotonous after a while. Any combat scenario pretty much is a re-run of spreading your guys out a little, using snipers to pick off people before they get to your party and then resorting to assault rifles / laser weapons to finally take people down. Sure there are some scenarios which are different but generally any combat you enter will rely more upon your chance to hit rather than making much use of the landscape, unlike in other RPGs such as Divinity : Original Sin.The skill progression does not really give a sense of achievement when you level. You allocate points to various weapon proficiencies or skills which boosts your chance to hit, damage or likelihood of completing a task. I neglected to skill into some of the diaglogue skills (Smart♥♥♥♥♥ Kiss♥♥♥♥♥etc) and was a little disapointed when I encountered an NPC that would have offered new diaglogue options if I had applied my skills into these area.Overall its a solid game but nothing extraordinary. If you like RPG and love the post-apolcalypic setting then I would reccomend you pick it up when its next on sale. Just dont expect to be blown away."
