,Recommended,240760,12894955,"Posted: 11 November, 2014",all,Ver-y gay,"OverviewWasteland 2 is a sequel to the underappreciated Wasteland title; so underappreciated, that it took two-and-a-half decades for its well deserved sequel to come to light.While it may be a sequel to Wasteland, Wasteland 2 differs greatly from its predecessor. While it drops nearly every mechanic used in the first iteration, it uses that opportunity to rebuild the core experience, which has been shown to have been for the best.-RPG-ElementsI'd rather leave this short, so I'll try to generalize this as simply as I can. RPG in the elements seem to combine the best of elements from games like Final Fantasy and Fallout, each character is unique in the way it levels up and unlocks new skills. It allows lots of room for experimentation and you never feel to pressured about making the wrong choice.8/10-CombatDepending on the type of player you are, combat will be either an tense, enjoyable experience, or a half-hearted ""meh."" To start, there is a very loose leash when it comes to options, ranging from different weapons such as Knives and blunt objects, to more exotic sorts such as Laser Pistols and Plasma Beams. I always felt like there was something new I could try with every instance of combat, which is unique in of itself. I was even more surprised to find that every one of these options is viable given the proper situation. Even though I have a rather negative opinion of melee weapons, I found myself dedicating one of my four squadmates to the art entirely. My only complaint towards combat was that as the game shifts into the phase of 20 - 30 hours of playtime, enemies become more predictable than a horror movie, with their patterns becoming quickly memorized as they fail to differ from the usual, ""Find the closest cover, and shoot."" tactic.8/10-StoryWithout saying too much, the story can be viewed as slightly above average. While it can be both funny and serious at times, I found it hard at times to get myself fully immersed in the games story. A saving grace for this however, is the absolutesuperbvoice acting.7.5/10ConclusionThere's not much bad to say about this game, aside from the occasional glitch or two, the devs are working hard at keeping this game up to date. And all in all, I find this a great throwback to the old Point-&-Click RPG games of my childhood. Great team. Great Game. And they deserve your interest and money.7.9/10"
