76561198046711798,Recommended,240760,13289806,"Posted: 8 December, 2014",all,Jared Kushner,"9.5/10This is the successor to Fallout 1 & 2 that I have been waiting for since 1998. The mechanics of the game are a lot different, but it captures that post-apocalyptic feeling I love. There are a number of glitches, and the graphics are mediocre, but those criticisms were also applicable to Fallout 1 & 2, two of my favorite games of all time.I never played Wasteland 1 because I was too young when it came out, and by the time I was interested it was just too difficult to figure out the interface and other game mechanics. I am familiar with the plot of the original however, and this seems like a faithful sequel to the original as far as I can tell.If you have any interest in turn based games, post-apocalyptic themes, or old school RPGs, buy this game. Normally I wait to buy games on Steam after they've gone on sale, but I paid the full asking price for this game and have no regrets whatsoever. Worth every penny. Over 100 hours in and I've barely cracked the surface - though admittedly that included a number of restarts because I am a bit of a perfectionist. This game has so much content, so much goodness, that any valid criticisms of the game evaporate."
