76561197993783476,Recommended,240760,12571186,"Posted: 19 October, 2014",all,EchoStarter,"10/19/2014. At least 100 hours of actual play time clocked as of this review.Might not be for everyone, but it's a good solid game. Requires a decent amount of time investment. 8/10YOU MIGHT LIKE THIS GAME IF- You like creating custom teams- You like long rpg games- You like tactics games- You like post-apocalyptic themesWHAT I LIKED ABOUT THE GAME- Character creator is in-depth enough.- Combat is decent enough.- Decent difficulty level. You don't get to just breeze through everything. You need the right stats and the right items to accomplish certain parts of the game. Really makes you be observant of your environment.- Your characters don't become overwhelmingly powerful. You always have to be careful and employ some degree of strategizing (e.g. unit placement, wepon equipment, team composition).- Story is generic, but engaging enough.- Your characters stats and skills are actually useful. There's a skill called ""Fix Toasters""... and it's actually useful for something.- Gives you the option to add notes to your quests (which already have a decent description). These can be helpful to remind yourself about what you need to do or what course of action you may want to take when tackling a quest.WHAT I DIDN'T LIKE ABOUT THE GAME- Mainly UI issues.- Item management could be better, but it's nowhere near game-breaking.- Some rare glitches with the screen scrolling. When in combat, sometimes you can't scroll the screen. This can sometimes prevent you from clicking on your target. You have to wait for an enemy to attack you before the scrolling kicks in again. I'm sure it can be fixed with an update.- Sometimes, I felt like some of the missions/quests/storyline dragged. But, it was rare and may be expected of long rpgs."
