,Recommended,240760,14807517,"Posted: 9 March, 2015",all,kobolde,"Well, I'm kind of torn about this game. On one hand it's an excellent game, with a decent story, fun combat, interesting skills to use and well-enough made. But there are a million of annoying things, which don't really ruin the game for me, but bug the hell outta me. The game does have some very good ideas, for example looting enemies is well done; you automatically loot nearby enemies when selecting one, and you can send loot across the party to Rangers who can use the found ammo, medi-kits, etc. Also the conversation system is rather good. You can involve all of your group in a conversation, if you want to (not that it matters who speaks, but gives me an opportunity to roleplay my group). I'm still on my first playthrough, but I've already noticed there are almost always several ways to complete a task. Which is wonderful, not only for replayability's sake, but makes me feel I can do things my way.But the annoyances? They are aplenty. For example, no group formation. Seriously? The game is even designed so that battles start where the characters stand, so every fight I have to start with all my characters clumped together. And you can't even move through other characters!! Very frustrating. Another big problem with combat is that I can't postpone a characters turn. This is especially annoying when my Ranger gets to act first when combat begins, but she is surrounded by her team mates, and cannot move. This added to the fact that hitting your own teammates by accident seems a little too easy, and it gets frustrating fast. This kinda omissions should have been patched a long time ago, I can find no excuses why they are still in the game.There are other gripes, also. The logbook for one is next to useless. There are only two sorting options, both of which make very little sense. And in this kind of game, I would expect that I could check the log for all the conversations I've had. But no. You can't even manage the logbook in anyway, except for tagging some tasks. I have a task regarding some objects I found, and after running around for over an hour, I finally checked the quest from the internet, and found out that I can't complete it, because the guy I was supposed to talk to was now dead. But I can't remove the task from the logbook even manually. Adds to frustration.A big problem is also the enemy AI. There is none, seems like it is artificial stupidity rather than intelligence. Enemies have no tactics or sense of self-preservation. Usually they just rush you and get killed.So, in closing, the game is rather good, but has a million small problems, which aren't that bad alone, but start to eat you up eventually. Oh, and the humor seems rather forced, most of the jokes left me feeling ""meh"". I still recommend this, though.PS: Game of the Year 2014? Gotta to be a joke, Divinity: Original Sin came out the same year. Other than the setting, these two games are very similar, but D:OS is soooo much better made."
