,Recommended,240760,12217876,"Posted: 24 September, 2014",all,Marty McFlash,"Easily one of my favorite games of 2014.  It's a must play for fans of turn based Western RPGs.Pros:Fun turn based combat that's not overly tactical or complicated.Option to use custom portraits for your created characters.Interesting world and side stories.Some choices make a big impact on the game.Character building. There are no preset classes, your character is totally what you make them.  (although I should add that the game system really rewards min/maxing characters, so that could be a pro or con to you depending on your attitude towards that kind of thing)Cons:There can be a lot of running back and forth over area maps. The Rail Nomads quests in particular I found to be really tedious, as you have to make several roundtrips over a distance with no fast travel.Still an occasional bug here and there.3D Character models are really poor.  When viewed close up, like during character creation, it's like stepping back in time 10 years.  Not a major issue for a game like this though.The level up system requires you to make a radio call back to HQ every time someone levels up. At first it was kind of neat, and added a little flavor to the game.  It gets tedious later, because your characters level up at different rates. You might have 1 or 2 guys level up, make the radio call, skip through the dialogs, distribute skill points etc. Then a minute afterward, someone else levels up so you have to go through the radio call again.As you can see, my cons are all minor things or nit-picking. It's a good game, and worth your money even at the full price.  Definitely an Early Access gamble that paid off."
