,Not Recommended,240760,13078724,"Posted: 25 November, 2014",all,farmboy1536,"I would say don't buy this with some qualifiers.  IF you loved Wasteland 1, do not realy care about a ""real"" squad tactics game, or just want to kill some time, then by all means, purchase.  I did get some enjoyment from this game, and while the gameplay was linear, I expected it to be due to the emphasis on the story, and following that story.  Approach it like a book you get to play instead of read and many of the complaints reviewers express are put to rest.HOWEVER, if you wanted X-Com, JA, FOT, then this game is a weak sister by comparison.  Almost all my combat was to make a skirmish line just outside the enemy's engagement range, shoot a bad guy/thing/animal, then wait for all them to run at me one at a time to get shot up.  Stab the few melee jerks who get through (because the ranges of firearms is pitiful) and then loot. Almost no tactical skill needed.  Just draw them in, shoot them up, rinse and repeat.And they get GUNS WRONG!!  Augh!  I have so much hate for lazy guns when you have a combat game.  M-14's take 7.62x51 (I would have been ok with .308, but I digress).  M1 Garands take .30-06.  I am sure that for simplicitys sake they assigned weapons by class, and assigned one ammo type per class (of course, classing a full size rifle like the 14, Garand, G3/HK 91, or the FAL as an ""assault"" rife is an insult anyway).  Granted, in game some pistols/smg's took 9mm, but some took .38......  .38? WTF! Name one smg that was ever chambered for .38.  I know of one, ONE, auto-loading pistol that ever took .38 (special) and that is the Coonan.  Granted there is the .38 Super round that is an auto rim design, but let's face it, they were talking .38 Special in this game.  I could go on, but I'll quit here......  LAZY!The story was fine, but the decision process was very scripted.  There was little choice other than to go from A-B-C.  I am not really complaining about that, like I said, it is like you are reading a book, only playing it.  I could have handled a bit more of the ""find your own adventure"" style though.  It was nice to see what happened to the ""original gang"" from WL1.This game was like that ""Sir Robin"" from Monty Python's Holy Grail.  It was a story of almost.  They almost made a tactical game like JA, FOT, X-COm.  They almost made a FO 1-2 RPG, they almost made the post apocolyptic game I was expecting as a follow up for WL1.  What we got was WL1 (basically a text game) with animations for combat and you could see the whole party at once instead of a single character, with 3D instead of 2D.It is like wanting to eat Italian, but going to Olive Garden instead."
