76561198002259672,Recommended,240760,8060141,"Posted: 15 December, 2013",all,Grinning Zero,"From starting the game and playing for a few hours I personally can say I like this game. This review is my opinion and all others are entitled to their opinion. Now then......The game itself is a continuation of the old wasteland classic and the original is considered the godfather of post-apocalyptic rpg games, that in itself is more or less true. A game to compare this to would be the original fallout games 1 and 2. Both of which were developed by Brian Fargo and his team, I considered them to be great games and more addicting than most of todays mediocre games. So far this game is in beta but from what I played it will hopefully continue to get better.-Combat is pretty simple. Ammo and weapons as well as armor and abilities all play major factors in this game. If a party member runs out of ammo they dont auto-reload, reloading is done manually. Melee is pretty self-explanatory, just close range and knock the enemy down. As far as combat goes it is wise to put experience towards what your characters are proficient in as it can help out a lot but variety works too.-The game world is just like the original fallouts and wasteland in which you move your party across a map to various locations while avoiding radiation hotspots and coming across random encounters. Water is important! Your party will need water to keep traveling otherwise they will die at some point.-Dialogue is interesting and if you can deal with reading text it brings a lot of backstory into the game about your mysterious enemy.-Sound effects and music are great. I found myself at one part cringing when a group of soldiers were panicking and screaming after they were attacked by an enemy with chainsaws.-Art and environment are beautiful, and naturally in my opinion graphics dont make a game and with the increasing technology and race for better graphics I find most games nowadays to just be pretty light shows anymore.-The price is steep for a beta yes, however.....this was done because of the amount of money some backers put up on kickstarter and in trying to not♥♥♥♥♥♥of those who already backed this game, that is why this game is $60. In my mind its understandable but a lot of other people would disagree.-The only game breaking bug Ive found is when loading a save that none of my characters will move or do anything at all but yet other npcs and whatnot still move around and music and everything still play just fine. Ive come across no other issues so far.Final Verdict: Overall Im enjoying this game alot. Im a fan of fallout 1 and 2 as well as the original wasteland. The price is steep but I can't include that in the final verdict. I found it comical the little prank played in the main menu about the dlc (there is no dlc by the way) which in itself was very clever since most companies now sell day 1 dlc. So without further ado aside from the game breaking bug I would say this game falls into about an 8/10 due to the bug and the fact this game is still in beta. Some might think this score is way too high but this is my opinion, for anyone interested in whether or not they'd like this game well they'll have to find that out themselves."
