,Not Recommended,240760,16700727,"Posted: 25 June, 2015",all,Saeheria,"This game is like Fallout 2 and Fallout: Tactics had a baby, only that baby got dropped on it's head a whole lot during development.This game is not billed correctly, it is a tactical shooter with rpg elements.  The ""choice"" seems limited to one major decision, and the skills leave you in fear of putting points down.  What if I need my lockpicking higher in the next room?  I'll wait and see.  This is how half my party ended up with massive skill point pools they were just holding onto.  The UI is clunky, in order to interact with an object the correct party member needs to be selected, the correct ability needs to be selected, and then you need to interact with the object.  If you screw up the order or misclick: BOOM.  A bomb usually goes off in your face.  I would have liked to have seen a system where you could just click on the object and have the appropraite skill used, since the way it is set up just promotes quick saving and loading; i have absolutley blown myself up just because I clicked the wrong thing.The characters themselves are pretty bland with few exceptions where the dialogue really got given some love, which is another reason I don't feel like this is a real rpg.  I've encountered characters who were named simply to give them names.  I have mixed feeling about this, on the one hand it's great for everyone in the world to be a unique person, but I would prefer to be able to interact with them.  This was made even stranger when I encountered other people who were just called ""Townie.""   It seems almost as though the game was rushed into the final stages of development in order to remove the early access title.In my opinion the game is not worth a buy at full price, I managed to get it on sale at 50%, and played 26 hours, so I don't feel like I was ripped off, I've payed 60$ for games that were worse and their total duration was a quarter of that.  If you can get it on sale and like a top down shooter, pick it up, but don't expect a diverse rpg world, just killing."
