76561198082935611,Recommended,240760,31095712,Posted: 12 April,all,zombogeekz,"So, I am a fan of turn based strategy/adventure games and this game makes the cut.It's entertaining, dark, and dystopian. Think Xcom meets Fallout.I thoroughly like this game's story, both of them.That's really a problem actually. The first half of the game takes place in one location, and the second takes place in a completely different location. Once you move past one, you can't come back. It's very much like there are two games.Also, the tactics for the first location are killing with normal conventional weapons and that's mostly thrown out the window in the second half, making all of your character development pretty much useless.The mechanic for gaining new ability points is pretty stupid. You must choose high intelligence in order to gain abilities. If you don't, your characters will be severely left behind by the later stages, and get screwed because of that.So not only do you have to know that going into creating a character (and it's not obvious while doing so) you also have to set your characters up with two different and contradictory styles of fighting to advance with the characters you like.It's not very intuitive.The acheivements are glitchy and sometimes require you to restart from a previous save and they're also not very good. You have no choice but to save before every major decision and reload multiple times to get all of the acheivements.I know that's meant for replayability but lets face it, this game is only good enough for one play through and that's it.Still, I would buy this game. However not unelss it's on sale for 90% off at least.7/10"
