,Recommended,240760,22650455,"Posted: 26 April, 2016",all,LP STorytime,"Wasteland 2 throws you into post-apocalyptic turn-based combat.The story isn't anything new; a land being ravaged, once again, by a robot army. The story flows nicely, being held up by interesting characters and a variety of environments which you explore. As the setting begins to become stale, you are thrown into a new part of post-apocalyptic America to continue your journey.Leading a squad you have created through each new location of the game, the areas and enemies change frequently enough that it all feels new. With the different combinations of weapons and skills for your characters moving you forward to the next slew of combat.Combat is strong in this game. The variety in your strategy is determined by the development of your characters and the new enemies thrown your way. Whether keeping a sniper in cover on a hilltop or rushing forward a bruiser with a crowbar, there is plenty of variety inbetween. Any combat scenario you encounter can be approached in a number of different ways.If you enjoy post-apocalyptic landscapes and turn-based RPG's, buy this game."
