,Not Recommended,240760,19008375,"Posted: 11 November, 2015",all,jimwinsor,"I really wanted to like this game, and I tried really hard to do so. But in the end its numerous flaws were too pungent to ignore:1) A really dumb combat system. Now don't get me wrong, there are tactics involved, mainly dealing with the positioning of your characters in such a way as to avoid friendly fire. But that's about it. The rest of it is just standing in open ground, and plugging and/or slashing away at the nearest target.Yes there is a smattering of ""cover"" here and there you can shield yourself from fire with, but animals and melee units are able to pretty much run up to you in one turn with impunity, and attack you regardless. And they always seem to run up to you in such a way as to place your other characters in the line of fire, necessitating you to move away to avoid friendly fire.So yeah, there are ""tactics"" here, an elaborate dance where you move your guys around the map in such a way as to shoot the enemy without shooting your teammates in the back. Ie, tactics that bear no resemblance to combat tactics in real life.2) The artwork is just cheap, horrible and amateurish. And some of the portraits don't match the character descriptions, and many are reused for other characters, just simply destroying game immersion. For a $40 buck game, the consumer deserves better.3) The number of times you have to go back to a previous save because you accidentally triggered combat with friendly NPCs is utterly frustrating, and just indicative of a terrible design.Like I said, and really wanted to like this game. The original turn-based Fallout games were some of my all time favorites back in the day, and I was so hoping this game would pick up the torch. Instead they fumbled it."
