,Recommended,240760,12534310,"Posted: 17 October, 2014",all,Slammus,"Lets cut to the chase shall we? Youre here looking to see if this game is ball or if its worth you hard earned steam munnies. I wont sugar coat it honey, these are simple facts.When it comes to survival, it is a little lacking unless played on harder difficulties. The fact that you get 4 team mates to help out means you can distribute the skills accordingly so no skill-based action will be difficult. You've got your basics skills: your doctor, your blowey-uppey guy, you smooth talker, and your hackey-stealy guy. Basically if you could make four Fallout characters at once. Not to mention the game hands you extra characters that have the skills you thought were useless (get to the native american girl, you'll see) and there ya go. Free pass. In fact the only reason you may lose a fight is if you sold all yer loot for a badass pistol so you can kill even MORE people in 1-2 shots. Food is nothing, and water is not hard to find. literally. its the easiest thing if you allocate more than 3 points to your outdoorsey character.Next the fighting. Like i said before, 1-2 shots if you dont miss. This is changed alot by the difficulty, and reloading, but in all honesty those of you actually using this review to see if you want to buy the game will not be starting on sooper-gawdmode-h4x level. The fighting is simple and repetitive. the only changes are a cycle between four-five level schemes per fighting area and the enemies fought. oh theres some big toads that steal yer guns beeteedubs. so theres that. But when it comes to this game, do not buy it for the fighting.On to gameplay. This game is a good immerser, regardless of the simplicity of it all i felt actually effected by decisions i made in game, and you do not get long before you start getting those decisions. The story thus far is decent, but i havent beaten the game quite yet. ill get back to ye on tha one m8.Graphics, dont even. they are okay but you know.... just okay.Lets Recap:Survival: 3/10While you may have to skip things because you dont have the skill, you could come back later. Water is abundant, food is unneccesary, and health packs are literally everywhere. Unless on a harder difficulty that is.Fighting: 4/10While sometimes fun, it gets quite dull and repetitive. Dont be surprised when you inwardly/outwardly groan when some foamy mouthed bandits decide to try and jump you with STICKS without taking into account that you are all wearing armor made of super-metal. Just keep that mouse hovered over ""Sneak past em m8""Story/immersion: 8/10The story is well written, the choices are set in stone and there is normally no wrong answer. with side quests everywhere you can always expect to have one or two things to do at one time.All in all, if you're looking for a good action story in which you shoot da baddies, then go right ahead and click that buy button. The story is quite literally the only reason im rating this up, but by no means is it a bad game.Toodles~"
