76561198002971567,Not Recommended,240760,18276735,"Posted: 1 October, 2015",all,bombastinator,"I only just learned of the upcomming DLC so this is likely too late, but whiule the game is very good, it has some glaring drive-me-insane issues, and it sounds like the directors cut is not addressing them.  The changes made to directors cut I have read about, while nice do not sound like thery fix these issues.1) random and innacurate weapon behavior.  Someone appears to have assumed that the older a weapon is the worse it's performance.  While this is true in IT, it is NOT true of any weaponry made after about 1930, when powder technology matured the way cpu technology did in around 2008.  improvements are incremental.What changes is the method of warfare, and therefore you have weapons tailored to different types of combat.  If the type of combat gotten into is of an older fashoin newer weapons often UNDER PERFORM older ones.  The type of round fired is much more important to performance than gun design.The various weapons have names of current models, but they do not follow the actual properties of these weapons at all.The M2 is not a small bore machine gun. it fires .50bmg not 22cal ammunititon.  You could fit the intore barrel of a >5.56mm weapon inside the bore of a 12mm gun like the m2.this is actually a pretty easy fix.  A renaming and a new description are all that are required.  You could modify an m2 very easily to fire small bore ammunition.  It's a straight blowback weapon with huge pieces.  making stuff smaller is much easier than adding metal, so it could concievelably be a normal conversion for 50cals with worn out parts.It was designed origionally as an anti tank weapon, and cannot even be fired from a light vehicle without risking tipping the thing over.  It should be at the top of the food chain rather than the bottom, and have an incredibly high strength requirement.the 5.56 is actually a very powerful high pressure round.  Using it as a base ammo is a bit silly.  remington 223 is similar but lower pressure and civilian weapons like hunting rifles designed for 223 are often incapable of firing 5.56, though generally a 5.56 gun is capable of firing 223.meanwhile the easiest to produce, most common longest produced round in existance which DOES fit the characteristics of the low end weapons is the .22 long rifle round.  There ARE assault type rifles that use it, by far the most common in the US where the game is set being the ruger 10/22.  it si effectively identical to the m14 so the same models could be used.Meanwhile the m1 garand is not a 5.56mm weapon but 30.06 or 7.62 weapon, and is really a fast firing sniper rifle.2) The game's randomisztion and travel sytem requires huge amounts of reloading and downtime to play.Loot in theis game is massively random.  to the point that game difficulty is more dependant on random chest results than difficulty level or player ability.  As a result, the only effective way to play the game is saving/reloading on chests.  repeatedly.  I would say I spend 80% of playtime repeatedly opening the same chest, or digging the same hole.  also, spending 20 minutes following a tortise?!  There must be someone on staff who treasures the unparraleed joy of rush hour traffic or something."
