,Not Recommended,240760,19001748,"Posted: 10 November, 2015",all,chimpansteve,"I really want to recommend this game - the first couple of hours were very enjoyable, the Director's Cut improvements actually seem to have fixed many of the original issues...but it's STILL an unfinished game, even after forever in Kickstarter and a 'final' edition. It's basically a game where the developers got most of the way through, then just thought 'sod it, that'll do'. It's effectively broken in most of the sidequests, and unbelievably frustrating for the rest. Buy it in a sale for a fiver - don't spend any more on it.Pretty much every sidequest is bugged so you can't complete fully. The interface means you'll frequently be unable to target enemies, even when in open ground. Dialouge is more often than not nonsensical. There's what initally seem trivial but turn into mindbending frustrating issues with the inventory - basic stuff like being unable to sort by weight or value, or sell all items in a stack, or other basic things that were sorted in RPGs decades ago. The map and journal are aggressively unhelpful. You'll be forced into quicksaving every couple of minutes as the companion AI is so bad, and you can so easily unintentionally ruin a quest due to the terrible dialogue options. Tedious and repetitve 'random encounters' (which are anything but) on the world map make travelling a chore. There's a total lack of polish throughout (for example, every hat, say a 'metal helmet', has a stetson model. None of the clothing options display on your character model. Your guns don't line up properly. Item descriptions are frequently missing or half finished).Most of these complaints may sound trivial, and I have never played the original so may be missing any familiary or tolerance for the interface others may have, but the irritaions quickly add up and end up destroying any form of immersion. There's the core of a very good game in here, but it's just too frustratingly unfinished to recommend, sadly."
