,Not Recommended,240760,23486461,"Posted: 10 June, 2016",all,Antonius Palatinus,"Rewiews keep telling that this game is like Fallout, and this is very much untrue.I remember walking by a small village made of junk and rust, treading heavily in my power armor. Children were playing around, and the wasteland sun was shining. One kid threw a stone at me, it clancked off my shoulder plate. I decided to play along, picked that stone up and threw back at the kid, my hand accelerated with well-oiled X-series power armor motors. The stone went right through kid's body, he screamed and fell into a puddle of his own blood and entrails. Suddenly i became an all-hated child murdering psycho, but what did i care, i had a Bozar on my back, helload of ammo and iguana on a stick. Terrified villagers heard my helmet-muffled whistling as i walked away, towards the white wasteland sun and new exciting adventures.That's one of my many Fallout memories, and the only memory that Wasteland 2 left is gosh that sucked.Wasteland 2 is on a level of really good tablet or smartphone game. It's built on awful Unity engine, which screams lazyness, it has a tablet-level dumb combat system, bland graphics with no textures, you name it...The plot and setting are extremely uninspired, if you are a veteran of Fallout franchise, you will feel a very strong deja vu.Mutant plants on a food growing facility? Nuclear bomb worshipping fanatics? Robot army? Raiders? Fanatics preserving technology? List could go on but i didn't make it to the end of the game.Quest system is tedious and lacks logic. I remember doing a lot of quests to make peace between two gangs in some village, even did some not obvious things, like disarming bomb on a bycicle quickly, but in the end they still shot each other, i checked on the internet and realized it's all because i didn't kill(on purpose) some drugs producing guy, who had nothing to do with the rivalry!Though i liked some non-obvious thing in game, like strange creature in a cell which asks for candy, strange person standing in a pointless location, it's very rare in modern quest markered games with no mystery to them.Overall, i don't recommend this game to Fallout fans, because it's nothing like it."
