,Recommended,240760,12214829,"Posted: 23 September, 2014",all,ineedbettername,"Oh my god yes. This game takes almost everything that people loved about Fallout 2, and adds *more* player agency. If you crit failed a lockpick check, there's always the option to just break down the door or kick the crate to pieces. If you're put below 0 HP, you're not instantly dead as in most other games. Instead, a character can either be knocked unconscious, in which case they'll revive themselves for 1 HP a turn until positive health, or be bleeding out, losing 1 HP per turn until death.In that state, a character can be revived by another with the Surgeon skill, or finished off by a particularly sadistic enemy. Unfortunately, I have yet to encounter NPCs that use this mechanic, leading me to believe that it's a player hand-holding device. I would love to see this implemented for higher difficulties, since it would make the combat that much deeper.Also, you can legitimately spend skill points on ""Toaster Repair"". And it's worth it. They can have awesome loot in them!"
