76561198076481122,Recommended,240760,12652446,"Posted: 26 October, 2014",all,ianmason96,"This game is great and one of the rare must-plays of an RPG fan. Consequences are treated realistically, and sometimes (read: sometimes) you will have to make important ethical decisions that will screw certain factions over in favor of other ones. The companions have interesting dialogue that makes it hard to hate them, and more often than not, you will find yourself genuinely moved. Keep a few alternate save slots- you will want to see how everything ends.Protips for best ending: Chaos is almost never good. Invest in Smart♥♥♥♥♥and Kiss♥♥♥♥♥skills.It's to be notedThat being said, there are two major gameplay flaws. Number one is the enemy move range. When the enemy moves, they, more often than not, will move halfway across the map in order to reach you, stand out in the open exposed like an idiot, or both. I admit, the obscene move may be so they can get to you, because without it they likely would be taking 2-3 turns to get into range. But, I fought most of my fights in an old British-style line formation, because the enemies didn't let me get a chance to get into cover! And no, the player characters can't move that fast.Number two is the allied units' AI. Like the enemies, they will move obscene distances to get within range of the target, but when a friendly sniper tries to run up, out of your units' move and attack range, to melee an opponent that can kill him/her in one hit when he still has ammo in his clip, you know something's wrong with the AI. If you don't want to see allies die, my advice would be to not recruit them. (This applies to random people you meet on your adventures that want to temporarily aid you, not recruitable party members that count towards your party limits. With minor exceptions, they should remain under control.) This, however, is a minor flaw, as friendly NPCs are rare.Don't get discouraged, though. I love this game, its multiple paths and otherwise tight combat MECHANICS are good. Tactics is an important part of the game, and positioning before a fight can have many benefits. The ending slideshow bugs have been largely fixed, and the game runs well."
