,Recommended,240760,12200823,"Posted: 23 September, 2014",all,Undeadenemy,"If you played and enjoyed the original Fallout 1 and 2, or if you played the original Wasteland (I haven't), you will love this game.Even if you haven't played any of those, Wasteland 2 is still a great game. It's a fairly hardcore isometric party based RPG with turn-based combat. There are many different skills to choose from, but it never felt like there were too many. Each one is useful, and you really won't regret putting points into any of them. Also, you get to start with a party of 4, and you can custom build each character including their appearance and background history. I named all of mine after friends, making their attributes in ways that they might actually be if they were in the wasteland.Combat is turn-based, and feels a little like X-COM. The rest of the exploration is real time, and you travel the world via a map, where you can have random encounters. Be careful, if you one character has to fire through a tile a friendly character is standing on, there is a chance for friendly fire!Overall, the game is a lot of fun, and after 20 hours, I'm really enjoying it. The developer clearly has a sense of humor, and there are tons of cultural references in the game, and even on the main menu. Check it out, you won't be disappointed."
