76561198075237211,Recommended,240760,11387596,"Posted: 24 July, 2014",all,Bones,"Wasteland 2 is a throwback but it never feels outdated. The interface definitely needs some work but overall, it is an involving experience. The tactical combat feels similar to what XCOM did recently. It is satisfyingly brutal and also quite challenging. I love that your choices are impactful, and if one of the followers you pick up along the way dies, they stay perished unless you revive them in time. This makes for tense battles akin to old-school rpg's.The graphics are smooth and polished, with some pretty great colors and lighting. You will come across a wide range of environments and npc's. Enemies vary from infected violent animals to trigger happy raiders, environments from vibrant woods to dreary basements and ""dungeons"". There is a lot to take in here, and that is quite refreshing to see.Overall, with some polish and feedback taken, this game would be a breath of fresh air and surprisingly so. It feels quite derivative at times, but all of the pieces fit together masterfully. I would reccomend this to any rpg fan.Most like: if fallout had stuck to the top view, this is where it would be today."
