76561198025236070,Recommended,240760,12439595,"Posted: 10 October, 2014",all,Tyrian Phoenix,"It's alright.The story itself is... interesting.  I will say that there were some pretty cool things that happened and I did like the times when there really wasn't a good choice as I would expect from a post-apocalyptic setting.  The character dialogue was also a lot of fun and there's a lot of references to bascially everything ever.Need to go through again to figure out of fixing toasters is worth it...  Occasionally buggy but only game breaking once.  Certain weapons are useless in most occasions early game and others are nearly completely useless late game.  Don't bother with heavy weapons unless you want to shoot all your expensive ammo less accurately and for less damage than an assault rifle.  The crit rates and multipliers on brawling seem to be balling out of control.  10-20 dmg critting for 150 dmg on most attacks seems a little absurd to me... Not that it wasn't awesome.  Armor is marginally useful right up until it gets you killed.  Late game, you won't be dodging most attacks so good luck with that no HP build.Because hit rates and crit rates for weapons are primarily determined by skill ranks which you get more of from having a high Intelligence and health and carry weight are determined by Strength,  Intelligence and Strength are the two most useful stats.  Coordination follows in a distant third because it increases your available AP fastest.  Awareness is useful if you want to be able to move before your enemies shoot you to pieces and Speed is useful on melee characters so that you can run farther though the evasion increase is negligible.Biggest Complaints - Energy Weapons don't crit... unless the enemy is using one.  Also, you can't skip animations or cinematics so things can become a little tedious.  And considering how often you're going to end up fighting...  Suffice to say that I spent most of my time in combat.Favorite Follower - Takayuki ""Robot Fighting Heaven""Hit or Miss - You may be save scumming...  A lot."
