,Recommended,240760,12455456,"Posted: 11 October, 2014",all,Sigfried,"If this looks like a game you want to play, then it is a game you want to play.The developers hit all the right notes, especially if you take the time to play into the game's second half. I never played the original (which is included) but its clear this game does all it can to stay true to both the setting and story of that title while creating a modern game of some depth.If you need your games to be AAA quality, you might take some issues with the graphics or voice acting. The visual design feels rough, though careful examination shows great detail. The voice acting comes and goes, usually introducing a character with a bit of spoken dialog and then going text only.The story is not exceptional in its overall arc, but the lives of individual NPCs and locations are often compelling and amusing. There is a lot of character in the game with both great NPCs you can join up with and bizarre folks making their way in the wastelands.Combat is good, though has some rough edges. Armor is fairly pointless on higher difficulties and simply getting the best guns you can find trumps nearly every other consideration much of the time. But there is depth in the skills side that makes character building and development compelling. What is likely a first fight for many groups is exceptionally tough and is not optional. (my hint, bring explosives)  Overall difficulty comes in waves, getting easy when you get some spiffy new guns, and brutal when you wander into a new area and are not ready for  what waits there.You will be getting a good amount of game for your money. I was worried it was a bit sparse until it became clear there was a second half to the story. It left me satisfied and eager for a second playthrough on the highest difficulty taking some roads not taken the first time around, always a good sign."
