76561197978479111,Recommended,240760,12282822,"Posted: 28 September, 2014",all,Rezel,"Fan of Fallout 1 & 2? Buy this gameliked XCOM? Buy this gameno idea what the hell a turn based rpg game is and hate them.... well go away then...The first screen where you make your characters is very overwhelming due to a giant spreadsheet of info they throw at you when you create your characters, i think this is a bit off putting if you want to create your own characters, however I'd suggest just take the premades or just make some quick characters (dont spend too much time figuring out what each skill does on this screen learn in game what does what) and jump in till you get past the first two character levels (about 10 mins or so depending if your talking to EVERYONE), at that point you'll understand enough about the points and stats to make a real custom set of characters.The story is very retro where you're the only guy who does anything and the world relies on you to fix its problems, but hey that make you importin and special and fits in with the story's progression.The games learning curve is a bit hard for the first few stepts, but onces you get past the tutorial/basics you wont have any issues picking out how to approach things.One of the games very interesting points it has is perma-death in it, not to where oh you got a random head shot you're gone for ever, but if you don't use the revive skill on someone after a set amount of time they will be gone and your now short a member. however they do have npcs you can recruit in some towns as well as some story npcs if you save them to give you more members.If i'm giving points my overall arbitrary number would be above 75's but below 90 out of a full 100, the game is good and would say its worth while to play, but the thing that really pulled me in was the nostalgia of playing an updated Fallout 1/2. Overall Wasteland 2 has a few points that could use improvement, such as the character creator (custom characters is always a big thing on my lists) needs a lot more options (it did support make your own character picture, but the ingame 3d characters i only found like 3 that were likeable) and the story has quite a few plot holes, but it does have good gameplay and interaction with the world depending on say your characters repair skill or free items from a store if you have high enough talk skill.My overall impression is this is a great game to pick up if you're into this style of play, but in no way is it going to turn you to like this style if you're not into it. the major thing that hurts the game is probably the current price point of the game that makes people on the fence about it."
