,Recommended,240760,12500518,"Posted: 15 October, 2014",all,fortuntek,"Quick and dirty review:I approve of Inxile, their roots and what they stand for, but I was discouraged from what I heard about early access ""missteps."" That said, after playing very little of Wasteland 2 I realized that it combines some of the best aspects of many of my favorite games of ALL TIME. Actually, probably most of them. Let that sink in.- Area exploration reminds me of Baldur's Gate series, including finding loot, unlocking/disabling traps.- Combat reminds me of XCOM, minus the focus on cover and more focus on consumables and abilities.- Narrative text reminds me of... nothing. Nothing has the same amount of flavour. Planescape: Torment, maybe.- Over-world exploration reminds me of the NWN2 Expansion, Storm of Zehir (only far better).- Creating all your characters from scratch gives me a bit of an XCOM or Final Fantasy Tactics vibe, only with the stat detail of a D&D game.- Obviously, atmosphere is very Fallout, only more fleshed out and in my opinion, better.This is just meant to be a quick run-down, but Wasteland inspired many of these games, or inspired the games that inspired them, and considering the past pedigree of Inxile's devs these influences are both understandable, and awesome.Small disclaimer: my taste in games seems almost custom tailored to Wasteland 2 so if you know not of what I speak, look elsewhere. If you found yourself nodding at these references, stop reading reviews and buy this game. Actually, do that anyway. I'm pretty sure it's going to go down as one of my next All-Time Favorites, maybe it'll be one of yours too."
